SIMPLE: self-starter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-starter
<hw>Self`-start"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mechanism (usually one
operated by electricity, compressed air, a spring, or an explosive gas),
attached to an internal-combustion engine, as on an automobile, and used
as a means of starting the engine without cranking it by hand; -- called
also a <altname>starter</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-sufficiency</ent>⟦br⟧
